store.sales = ggplot(head(cvs.1,20), aes(x = , y = sum)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  coord_flip() +
  theme(text=element_text(family="- ", size=12))

print(store.sales)

Group by Weekdays

See which day has the most sales number.

cvs.7 = group_by(cvs, weekday) %>% summarise(sum = sum()) %>% arrange(desc(sum))

# plot
weekday.sales = ggplot(cvs.7, aes(x = weekday, y = sum)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  coord_flip() +
  theme(text=element_text(family="- ", size=12))

print(weekday.sales)
